longBusinessSummary: DynaResource, Inc. acquires, invests in, explores, and develops precious and base metal properties in the United States. The company primarily explores for gold, silver, and other metals. Its flagship property is the San Jose de Gracia property with 33 concessions covering approximately 9,920 hectares located in northern Sinaloa State, Mexico. The company was formerly known as West Coast Mines, Inc. and changed its name to DynaResource, Inc. in November 1998. DynaResource, Inc. was incorporated in 1937 and is headquartered in Irving, Texas.
